### Step 3: Verify README structure

The README at `sdk/servicenetworking/Azure.Provisioning.ServiceNetworking/README.md` currently has the following sections:

| Section | Status |
|---|---|
| Getting started > Install the package | ✅ Present |
| Getting started > Prerequisites | ✅ Present |
| Getting started > Authenticate the Client | ⚠️ Present but empty (acceptable for provisioning packages — no change needed) |
| Key concepts | ✅ Present |
| Examples | ⚠️ Incomplete — missing `ApplicationGatewayForContainersSecurityPolicy` example |
| Troubleshooting | ✅ Present |
| Next steps | ❌ Empty — add content |
| Contributing | ✅ Present |

Use `sdk/keyvault/Azure.Provisioning.KeyVault/README.md` as the canonical reference for section formatting and tone.

---

### Step 4: Validate

Run these commands in order. Each must succeed before proceeding to the next:

1. `dotnet build sdk/servicenetworking/Azure.Provisioning.ServiceNetworking/`
2. `dotnet test sdk/servicenetworking/Azure.Provisioning.ServiceNetworking/ --filter TestCategory!=Live`
3. `eng/scripts/Update-Snippets.ps1 servicenetworking` — check `git diff` to confirm README snippet blocks were updated
4. `eng/scripts/Export-API.ps1 servicenetworking` — required only if public types changed (not expected here)
5. `dotnet format sdk/servicenetworking/Azure.Provisioning.ServiceNetworking/`

</details>

